SIMPLE: roguery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roguery
<hw>Rogu"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The life
of a vargant.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The practices of a rogue; knavish tricks; cheating;
fraud; dishonest practices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'Tis no scandal grown,⟦br⟧
For debt and <qex>roguery</qex> to quit the town.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Arch tricks; mischievousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rogueship</ent>⟦br⟧
